        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 4:27PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Society Hill, or 9 miles north of Hurtsboro. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hurtsboro, Society Hill, Uchee, Creek Stand, and Warriorstand.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
